					Biographies





Name
Description




							Yitzhak Ezer


					
							Mr. Yitzhak Ezer has been appointed Chairman of the Board at Paz Oil Company Ltd. effective September 21, 2016. Until this date, he served as Director at the Company from June 1, 2005. Mr. Ezer serves as a Partner, Accountant and Director at his own financial consultancy and accountancy firm. Mr. Ezer holds a LLB degree from The Interdisciplinary Center (IDC) Herzliya and a Bachelors degree in Accounting and Economics from Tel Aviv University. He is a Certified Public Accountant.




							Yona Fogel


					
							Mr. Yona Fogel serves as Chief Executive Officer at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since October 1, 2007. His work experience includes the following roles: Chairman of the Boards of Directors at Paz Industries and Services Ltd. and at Paz Ashdod Oil Refinery Ltd. (subsidiaries), Executive Vice President and Head of Banking Division at Bank Leumi Le Israel B.M., Senior Vice President of Marketing and Strategic Development at Bank Leumi Le Israel B.M. and Chairman of the Board at Leumi Card. Mr. Fogel holds a Bachelors degree in Psychology from Bar-Ilan University and a Masters degree in Psychology from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem.




							Sharona Novak


					
							Ms. Sharona Novak serves as Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since April 1, 2013. She also serves as Director at some of the subsidiaries of the Group. Her work experience includes the following roles: Corporate Controller Check Point Software Technologies Ltd. for seven years and Employee at the Tax Department at Kost Forer Gabbay & Kasierer. She holds a Bachelors degree in Accounting and Business Management from Hamichlala Leminhal. She is a Certified Chartered Accountant.




							Ilan Yefet


					
							Mr. Ilan Yefet serves as Finance Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since August 1, 2006. He also serves as Director at some of the subsidiaries of the Group. His work experience includes the following roles: Director at Pazomat Ltd. and Director at Paz Oils Ltd. Mr. Yefet is a Certified Public Accountant.




							Amir Erez


					
							Mr. Amir Erez serves as Chief Executive Officer at Pazgas Ltd., a subsidiary of Paz Oil Company Ltd., since May 1, 2013. He also serves as Chairman and Director at some of the subsidiaries of the Group. Prior to these roles, he served as Vice President Business Management and Services at the Refinery and Logistics Division of the Company for five years. He holds a Bachelor degree in Business Administration and Law from The Interdisciplinary Center (IDC) Herzliya.




							Shmuel Gotshal


					
							Mr. Shmuel Gotshal serves as Chief Executive Officer of Paz Aviation Services Ltd. and of Paz Aviation Assets Ltd., subsidiaries of Paz Oil Company Ltd., since October 30, 2005. Prior to this role, he served as Assistant to the Chief Executive Officer of these Companies. He holds a Bachelors degree in Economics from Tel Aviv University and a Masters degree in Public Administration from Auburn University at Montgomery.




							Haggai Zohar


					
							Mr. Haggai Gil Zohar serves as Chief Executive Officer of Pazkar Ltd. and of Paz Oil and Chemicals Ltd., subsidiaries of Paz Oil Company Ltd., since March 15, 2014. Prior to this role, Mr. Zohar served as Chief Executive Officer at Paz Oil & Chemicals Ltd. since February 1, 2004. Mr. Zohar holds a Bachelors degree in Industrial Engineering and Management from the Technion–Israel Institute of Technology.




							Moshe Sabag


					
							Mr. Moshe Sabag serves as Vice President for Information Technology, Human Capital and Administration at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since September 2010. His work experience includes the following roles: Vice President and Senior Staff Member at the Company (January 2005-September 2010), Information Technology Manager at the Company (January 1994-January 2005). Mr. Sabag holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science from the Technion - Israel Institute of Technology and a MBA degree from Tel Aviv University.




							Iris Penso


					
							Ms. Iris Penso serves as Vice President, General Counsel and Head of Risks at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since April 1, 2009. Her work experience includes the following roles: General Counsel at Danya Cebus Ltd., General Counsel and Corporate Secretary at Blue Square Israel Ltd. (October 2001-February 15, 2006), Head of the Legal Department, General Counsel and Corporate Secretary at various Blue Square subsidiaries, General Legal Counsel, Corporate Secretary and Assistant Director General to the President and Chief Executive Officer of Ace Marketing Chains Consumer Products Ltd. and Legal Counsel, Corporate Secretary and Management Member at Tempo Beer Industries Ltd. Ms. Penso holds a LLB degree from Tel Aviv University.




							Malachi Alper


					
							Mr. Malachi Alper serves as Vice President and Head of Refinery and Logistics Division at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since January 3, 2008. His work experience includes the following roles: Chief Executive Officer at Paz Ashdod Oil Refinery Ltd., Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Tnuva's Meat Division, Management, Strategy and Business Development Consultant, Chief Executive Officer at Klil Industries Ltd. (for one and a half years), Executive Vice President and Manager of Fine Ingredients Division in Frutarom Industries Ltd. (for three years) and Director of Business Development at Protech Ltd. (for three years). Mr. Alper holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Chemical Engineering from The Technion – Israel Institute of Technology, he completed a course in Business Management for Engineers at the University of Haifa and is a graduate of the Advanced Management Program (AMP) at Harvard University.




							Yoram Eyal


					
							Mr. Yoram Eyal serves as Vice President of Retail Operations at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since January 1, 2008. His work experience includes the following roles: Manager of the Filling Stations and Yellow Convenience Store Network at the Company (from 2002), Chief Executive Officer of Pazomat Ltd. (a division within the Company), Manager of Sales and National Operations at Elite-Strauss Group (now known as Strauss Group Ltd.), Manager of the Institutional Market at Elite-Strauss Group. Mr. Eyal holds a Bachelor of Business Administration degree from University of Derby.




							Uri Kahalon


					
							Mr. Uri Kahalon serves as Vice President of Real Estate and Operations at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since March 25, 2012. His work experience includes the following roles: Head of Real Estate and Operations at the Company for seven months, Head of Real Estate and Business Division at the Company for one and a half years, Director at some subsidiaries of the Company, Deputy Head of the Banking Division at Bank Leumi Le Israel B.M. for two years, Head of Marketing and Customers at the Retail Division at Bank Leumi Le Israel B.M. for three years. He holds Bachelor of Business Administration degree from Ramat Gan College.




							Israel Klepper


					
							Mr. Israel Klepper serves as Vice President of Wholesale at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since September 1, 2010. Prior to this role, he served as general worker and has held several positions over the years, including Northern District Manager, Manager of the Keshet Filling Stations Unit, Senior Deputy Vice President for Real Estate and Business Issues and Human Resources Manager. He holds a Bachelors degree in Social Sciences from the Open University and a MBA degree from University of Derby, Israeli branch.




							Miry Shaul


					
							Ms. Miry Shaul serves as Vice President-Communication and Regulation at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since March 19, 2015. Prior to this role, she served as Manager of Regulation and Company's spokeswoman from 2013. Prior to that, she served as Communication Consultant at the Environmental Office of Israel from 2009. She holds a Bachelors degree in Political Science from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem and a Masters degree in Law from Bar Ilan University.




							Pninit Colin Mass


					
							Ms. Pninit Colin Mass serves as Internal Auditor at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since July 1, 2013. Her work experience includes the following roles: Temporary Internal Auditor at the Company, Employee within the Internal Auditing Department at the Company and Employee within the Auditing Department at Bank National de Paris, Israel Branch for five years. She holds a Bachelors degree in Accounting and Economics and a MBA degree, both from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem. She is a Certified Chartered Accountant.




							Gavriel Rotter


					
							Mr. Gavriel Rotter serves as Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since November 24, 2010. His work experience includes the following roles: Co-Chief Executive Officer and Director at Castro Group for 20 years and External Director at FIBI Holdings Ltd. (November 2007-November 2010). Mr. Rotter holds a Masters of Business Administration degree from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem.




							Meira Git


					
							Ms. Meira Git serves as External Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since March 11, 2015. She is a member of the Audit, Compensation and Finance committees. Her work experience includes the role of Senior Assistant to the Chief Executive Officer of Bank Leumi for 42 years. Ms. Git holds a Bachelors degree in Economics and Political Science from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem.




							Efraim Sadka


					
							Prof. Efraim Sadka serves as External Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since August 4, 2010. He is the Chairman of the Audit, Compensation and Finance committees. His work experience includes the following roles: Professor of Economics at Tel Aviv University, Chairman of the Board of Directors at Shikun & Binui Ltd. (1989-1995), Chairman of the Board of Directors at K.G.M. Pension Fund (1996-2000), Director at Bank Leumi Le Israel B.M., Visiting Professor at The College of Management Rishon Letzion, Chairman of the Executive Board of The Pinhas Sapir Center for Development of Tel Aviv University, Chairman of the Supervisory Board at Poalim Real Estate Fund, Editor of The ‘Economic Quarterly’ (The Journal of the Israel Economic Association), Economic Consultant and Member and Chairman at various boards of directors. Prof. Sadka holds a Bachelors degree in Statistics from the Tel Aviv University and a Doctorate in Philosophy degree in Economics from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.




							Shaul Zemach


					
							Mr. Shaul Zemach serves as External Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since November 26, 2015. He is a member of the Audit, Compensation and Finance committees. His work experience includes the role of Chief Executive Officer at The National Water, Energy and Infrastructures Office of Israel (2009-2013). He holds a Bachelors degree in Economies and International Relations from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem and a Masters degree in Political Science.




							Revital Aviram Rabinowitch


					
							Ms. Revital Aviram Rabinowitch has been appointed Independent Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. effective July 20, 2016. She holds Directorship at various other companies. She holds a LLB degree from The Interdisciplinary Center (IDC) Herzliya, a Bachelors degree in Accounting and Economics from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem and a MBA degree from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem.




							Menachem Brenner


					
							Dr. Menachem Brenner serves as Independent Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. since May 28, 2014. He is a member of the Audit, Compensation and Finance committees. His work experience includes the role of Professor Lecturer for Finance at New York University for 23 years. Dr. Brenner holds a Bachelors degree in Economics from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem and a MBA degree, majoring in Finance, and a Doctorate in Philosophy degree in Finance & Economics, both from Cornell University.




							Arie Schor


					
							Mr. Arie Schor has been appointed Independent Director at Paz Oil Company Ltd. effective March 17, 2016. His work experience includes the role of Chief Executive Officer at Tnuva (2009-2016). He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science and a Bachelor of Engineering degree in Civil Engineering, both from The Technion – Israel Institute of Technology.











